# Odoo Development Workflow

When working on ANY Odoo task (modules, models, views, fields, OWL, security, migrations):

1. **Detect Odoo version first** — never generate version-specific code without confirming 14–19.
2. **Invoke context gathering** — use the Task tool with `subagent_type="generalPurpose"` and prompt it to follow `.cursor/skills/odoo-context-gatherer/SKILL.md` (or `~/.cursor/skills/odoo-context-gatherer/SKILL.md` when installed globally).
3. **Load patterns on demand** — read only the needed files from `odoo-development/reference/` via the Read tool. Do not preload all pattern files.
4. **Use the indexer** — for codebase lookups in Doodba projects, use the `odoo-indexer` skill before reading full source files.

Never skip context gathering before writing or modifying Odoo code.
